Hello, 
I would like to use LDAP user to connect to django MS SQL database. It works with SQL authentication but for Integrated Authentication (Windows Authentication) Django needs to have Kerberos ticket issued. I have changed DATABASES config like that:

```
DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'NAME': DBNAME,
        'ENGINE': 'sql_server.pyodbc',
        'HOST': DBHOST,
        'OPTIONS': {
            'driver': 'ODBC Driver 13 for SQL Server',
            'unicode_results': True,
            'Trusted_Connection': 'yes',
        }
    }
}
```

And Django makes attempt to use Integrated authentication but not having a ticket gives error:
`[ODBC Driver 13 for SQL Server]SSPI Provider: No Kerberos credentials available`

Is there any way that I can do "kinit" in Django so that I can use LDAP account so that Django can access its database? Would you be able to provide any example of Integrated authentication in Django?

The regular JSON encoders can't handle the Hashid object, so we had to override the encoder to use the hashed value instead of the instance:

````
class HashidJSONEncoder(DjangoJSONEncoder):
    def default(self, o):
        if isinstance(o, Hashid):
            return str(o)
        return super().default(o)
````

This is not that surprising or new, but I'd leave a note.

